Wait, maybe the problem is that when the model is first initialized, the first call to extend_pe is in __init__ with the init_tensor, but if we set the init_tensor to have a sequence length of 1, then the first pe would be of length 1, but then when the first actual input comes in with a longer sequence, the code will check if pe is sufficient. Wait, the code in extend_pe starts with:

if self.pe is not None:
    pe_length_required = x.size(1) * 2 - 1
    if self.pe.size(1) >= pe_length_required:
        self.pe = self.pe.to(dtype=x.dtype, device=x.device)
        return So if the existing pe's length is already sufficient, it can be reused.
